wikipedia_page.main: Granville Leveson Proby, 4th Earl of Carysfort  (14 September 1824 – 18 May 1872), styled Lord Proby from 1858 to 1868, was a British Liberal politician. He notably held office as Comptroller of the Household between 1859 and 1866.
